#: 5be851d2c4ac4b34a0699d11bec14466
msgid ""
"Pre-computes the signed distance field at mesh nodes and on a :math:`256 "
"\\times 256` regular grid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:129
#: dc729cac6bf64446afbc5583cc62594f
msgid "Draws random BCs subject to the validity constraints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:130
#: 94f81d9577c54a2496491a3b9d48c9e7
msgid ""
"Assigns boundary nodes to segments by parametric angle, builds per-"
"component Dirichlet / Neumann / Robin masks, evaluates BC functions at "
"nodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:133
#: 8f57921090214acba9ad817de9470bf8
msgid "Solves the PDE."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:134
#: 293f23d36af5436988d08f785e3849a0
msgid ""
"Computes harmonic extensions of the BC data (:math:`\\alpha, \\beta, g`) "
"into the interior — the neural operator consumes these as input features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:137
#: 348dba256ed640f6b057b306e47c2107
msgid ""
"Writes coordinates, solution, derived fields, SDF, and BC data into the "
"variable-length HDF5 schema."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:140
#: 4faf7be0fd2c4ac9bdcd9361f5b2fb48
msgid ""
"Roughly 100 lines of TensorMesh code do the actual FEM work; the other "
"~1500 lines are bookkeeping (random BC generation, segment assignment, "
"validity checks, HDF5 packing) — the dataset machinery that the original "
"FEniCSx code spends a similar fraction of its budget on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:148
#: 4736068a318346f691735381834f48d0
msgid "Where TensorMesh enters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:150
#: 28a1868f43f44b728775a476a7ca442c
msgid ""
"**Mesh generation** — :class:`~tensormesh.MeshGen` for the simple "
"geometries; raw Gmsh API for boomerang and the hollow geometries with "
"custom hole curves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:153
#: 978a048116464041b36e6268d245225b
msgid ""
"**Poisson solver** — :class:`~tensormesh.LaplaceElementAssembler` for the"
" stiffness; a custom :class:`~tensormesh.NodeAssembler` for the source "
"RHS; edge-based integration via :class:`~tensormesh.FacetAssembler` for "
"Neumann and Robin contributions; :class:`~tensormesh.Condenser` for "
"static condensation of the Dirichlet DOFs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:160
#: 9cbeb176fb94428a9d2390b3977c7162
msgid ""
"**Elasticity solver** — a custom Neo-Hookean assembler (same energy "
"density as :doc:`hyperelastic_beam`), L-BFGS energy minimization with "
"incremental loading, component-wise BCs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:163
#: 9712a36991e94549ac81f18260a2dc0d
msgid ""
"**Harmonic extension** — three extra Laplace solves per BC dimension to "
"extend boundary data smoothly into the domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/mousavi2026.rst:166
#: befc8044d68e4fd2b2396f30e6748b6e
msgid ""
"The fact that all of these speak the same TensorMesh API is what makes "
"the script readable in spite of its scope."
msgstr ""

